</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>When I'm reading the news online, the websites I gravitate toward are the ones that feature engaging visuals, uncluttered page layouts, and simple navigation options that make finding articles I'm interested in all that easier. I also tend to like sites with comprehensive editorial information so I know the articles I'm reading are well-researched and fact-checked.</p><p>News websites are virtual newsstands and, as such, they should have both great usability and visual appeal to grab users' attention. I've reviewed five sites that accomplish these essential goals, and if you're looking to create one of your own, try <a
href="/">Zarla's AI website builder</a>.</p></div><div
