class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="elle" class="entry-website-title">ELLE</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-3840x16013-20240723.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-3840x16013-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-3840x16013-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website ELLE"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.elle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.elle.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>New York, New York, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>ELLE is a global fashion magazine and news website covering a wide range of beauty, lifestyle, politics, and culture topics. I like the site's use of dark color accents and elegant typography as it creates a sophisticated appearance that bodes well with the company's audience. The large selection of articles, image galleries, and videos ensures readers have access to diverse content with engaging visuals to match.</p><p>A notable feature is that most of the website's content is free to access, encouraging readers to explore the site with no monetary incentive. There is an "All Access" subscription model available for users interested in receiving the print magazine.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site's clear categorizations ensure that the content remains uncluttered and easily readable. WAVE picked up only a few contrast errors throughout the website, enhancing the overall user experience.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>I don't have many complaints about this website, although I think some small tweaks should be made to the footer menu — enlarging the text would ensure easier readability, and highlighting the company's social media links would encourage increased user engagement.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-3840x16013-20240723.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-3840x16013-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On desktop, I think the website does a great job of showcasing the various articles and videos on well-spaced pages that make navigation all that easier. There's lots of white space to give the content sections ample breathing room, and the high-resolution images look great on a large screen. On Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the website received a good performance score of 76/100.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-20240723-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-elle-20240723-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile version gets rid of some of the horizontal white space to condense the website's content, which does not impact functionality or readability. While I found site navigation relatively straightforward, the top menu bar unsticks as you scroll down, which seems less intuitive than on the desktop. Google's PageSpeed Insights test gave the site a performance score of 58/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="goodness-exchange" class="entry-website-title">Goodness Exchange</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-3840x10053-20240723.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-3840x10053-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-3840x10053-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Goodness Exchange"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://goodness-exchange.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://goodness-exchange.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>St. Albans, Vermont, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Goodness Exchange is a media outlet that provides users with access to positive news articles from around the world, including content on business, environment, and technology topics. I enjoyed the website's sunny color accents, as well as its earth-inspired imagery, as it created an endearing appeal from the get-go and allowed me to better appreciate the nature of the content.</p><p>The website's home page gave me a great overview of the available articles and other content offerings, including free newsletters and podcast episodes. I also liked the "About" page for its in-depth introductory video and information on the company's team members.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's refined page layouts allow readers to easily access articles from various categories, enhancing the user experience. The site's pay-what-you-can subscription model is a unique feature that encourages readers to support the company's work in a sustainable manner.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>While my critiques of the website are limited, WAVE picked up a large number of contrast errors across the site. I also noticed that the footer menu advertises the company's social media feed, but it is not labeled as such, and a more prominent indication would be helpful.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-3840x10053-20240723.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-3840x10053-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop version functions well with fast page loading times, as indicated by its performance score of 74/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test. For readers wanting to sign up for the website, I found the registration process easy to follow. However, I don't think the site needs a hamburger menu on desktop, as all page links are accessible from the top menu bar.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-824x16382-20240723.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-goodness-exchange-824x16382-20240723.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile website's home page swaps a traditional hero image for a large tagline, which felt less impactful than its desktop counterpart. However, site navigation remained seamless and I liked how the content slims down to fit the smaller screens nicely. Performance-wise, our real-world tests indicated fast page loading times, but the site's PageSpeed Insights score was on the lower end of the spectrum at 32/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="the-narwhal" class="entry-website-title">The Narwhal</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-the-narwhal-3840x10329-20240723.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-the-narwhal-3840x10329-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-the-narwhal-3840x10329-20240723.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website The Narwhal"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://thenarwhal.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://thenarwhal.ca/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Victoria, British Columbia, Canada</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>The Narwhal is a Canada-based media company specializing in environmental journalism. The website favors minimalistic design elements, including a simple color palette and uncluttered top menu bar, to place the emphasis on functionality rather than over-the-top aesthetics. I liked the website's spacious layouts, which allow each article prominence without cluttering the page.</p><p>I also appreciated the company's approach to unbiased reporting with the "Our Ethics" section, which expands on its code of ethics and editorial independence policy.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>A notable feature for me was the site's "Trending Topics" section, which gives readers a quick overview of the most popular news topics across the country. WAVE reported no contrast errors on the website, indicating an intuitive reading experience.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>I could not find much to dislike on the website, but I'd have enjoyed seeing more visually engaging elements, such as video interviews or interactive content, to gauge my interest. The company logo could also be added to the top menu bar for increased brand recognition.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-the-narwhal-3840x10329-20240723.webp"
data-type="desktop"
